        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 2:29PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Pickens, or 5 miles southwest of Slater-Marietta,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greer, Taylors, Travelers Rest, Slater-Marietta, Paris Mountain State
Park, Tigerville, Lake Robinson, Pleasant Ridge State Park, Furman
University, and Berea.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
